[00:20] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'If you want to make cinematic music and scores for your films and videos, we\'re going to give you 13 tips, all using Video Composer inside Ace Studio, an AI music tool that completely completely changes the game for music creation. Let\'s go. Let\'s say you have a project'

[00:32] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'that you want original music for and you don\'t have time or money for a composer, but you also don\'t want to buy stock music because you want the score to actually be designed around what\'s happening on screen. You can use A Studio\'s video composer to generate'

[00:45] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'original music to perfectly match what\'s happening. Just drag and drop your video right under the canvas in A Studio. This will automatically create a video track. And if the video contains audio you don\'t want, just rightclick the video clip and click detach audio. You can'

[00:58] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'then edit, delete, or deactivate this audio as needed. From here, double click the video to open the video monitor. On the right side, open the AI agent, which is a chat style panel. Then type in a prompt for the style of music you want.'

[01:10] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'Create a music track in a Hollywood cinematic style with an epic ancient feel. Video Composer will analyze every scene, cut, and on-screen movement to generate a new original track to go along with your video based on your'

[01:22] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'prompt. You can then make further tweaks and edits until you get exactly what you want or generate an entirely new track until you get exactly what you\'re looking for. You don\'t just have to spray and pray'

[01:36] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'hoping you get what you want. Once you have a track, you have complete control to edit it via the timeline and mixer. Just create a new project and from here you\'ll see the canvas. This is where every track and clip in your project lives. You can move clips around, trim'

[01:48] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'them, duplicate them, mute or solo tracks, and line up musical hits with exact moments in your video. If you double click a clip, it opens the clip editor below where you can fine-tune audio, MIDI, lyrics, pitch, or vocal'

[02:00] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'controls depending on the clip. Then use the mixer to balance each track, adjust levels, add effects, and make the whole score feel like one finished piece. You also don\'t have to generate music'

[02:12] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'for your entire video at once. You can just select a time range on the timeline and the AI agent will only generate for that selected range. The selected time range shows up in the chat so it knows exactly where to generate. This is great'

[02:24] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'for when different parts of your video require different songs or music styles. You can also use Video Composer to generate sound effects by analyzing your video, creating sound effects for the entire thing, and putting them on a'

[02:37] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'timeline for you so that you can do sound design for your project all in one tool. In A Studio, you can make your own AI voices to sing and do vocals over your track. To create an AI voice using your own voice or a voice you have permission'

[02:50] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'to use, go to the custom voice page, choose a custom slot, and upload clean, dry vocal samples with no reverb, background noise, instruments, harmonies, or doubles. A studio will train a private voice model from those'

[03:03] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'samples. And once complete, it shows up in your voice library inside a studio. Then you can drag that voice onto the canvas, create a vocal clip, add MIDI notes and lyrics, and have your custom AI voice sing the part. A Studio also has an AI voice library of'

[03:18] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'community-made editable voices you can choose from. On the website, just go to creative library and under voices, you can preview voices in any style along with a singing sample. Save the ones you like by clicking collect and then you'

[03:30] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'can use them in your own projects. In addition to voices, there\'s a sample library with some incredible elements you can collect and use royalty-free in your own projects. Listen to this track by Stfano Macarelli called The Dark Is'

[03:42] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'Coming. So,'

[04:01] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'if you want a starting point for your own projects, you can go over to the'

[04:14] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'community a templates. Here\'s a template by Stfano Marelli again called The Sun is Going Down. You can then edit these templates to'

[04:43] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'make them your own inside a studio just like any track you make. You can even submit tracks you create to'

[05:10] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'a studio\'s creative library so that other people can use them in their projects. If you want to do the vocals yourself but have AI change your voice, you can use the vocal changer model. Just record it or import a vocal. Select the part of'

[05:22] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'the timeline you want to change. Open voice changer from the toolbar or right-click menu and choose a target voice or even an instrument sound. It will keep the melody and lyrics from your original take but change the character of the performance. You can'

[05:35] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'also customize your own voice changer voice by uploading samples to a custom slot, training it, and then opening it in a studio so it appears under the clone tab. You can also generate vocals from MIDI and lyrics with your own voice using the'

[05:48] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'vocal synth model. This is great if you don\'t want to record the performance at all. Just load an AI voice onto a track, create a vocal clip, draw in or import your MIDI melody, and type in the lyrics. A Studio will generate the sung'

[06:00] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'vocal from that melody and those words, and you can then edit the notes, lyrics, pitch, breath, and vocal controls to shape the performance. To customize your own, use vocal synth cloning. Just upload your vocal samples, train the'

[06:13] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'model, and then use that clone voice in the voice library, just like the built-in singers. If you already have a music track you like, but you only want certain elements, or you want to make changes to it, you can use the stem splitter. This'

[06:26] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'allows you to separate each individual instrument and vocal, and then mute or delete the ones you don\'t want, or edit them all individually. If you\'ve ever seen a mind-blowing movie trailer using an existing song, this is essential if you want to rework it to feel more'

[06:39] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'cinematic. If you already have a rough piece of music or even just a simple idea that isn\'t quite cinematic enough, you can use music enhancer to reimagine it. To select the audio on the canvas, click'

[06:57] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'music enhancer in the toolbar and a studio will analyze the music in style. You can then describe what you want it to become like symphonic orchestra, epic choir, cinematic strings. Adjust how closely it should follow the original'

[07:10] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'and click enhance. This is perfect when you like the melody or timing of a track but want it to feel bigger, more polished, or more trailer ready. One of the coolest things you can do in'

[07:50] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'A Studio is use AI instruments. Instead of loading a huge orchestral sample library, you can load an AI instrument from the instrument library, create an instrument clip, and feed it MIDI notes, A Studio turns those notes into a natural performance, and you still get'

[08:03] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'control over the details. You can choose instruments, build ensembles, edit the MIDI, and use articulations and expression controls to make the performance feel more human. So, for film scoring, you can quickly sketch strings, brass, or other layers without'

[08:16] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'needing to manually record anything. These are just a few of the things you can do inside A Studio and how you can use Video Composer to make incredible scores and music tracks for your films and videos. Go to astudio.ai to try it'

[08:28] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'out for yourself and we\'ll see you in the next one.'
